  ],
  "translations": {
    "en": "So the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him and his family) said: Where is the elder? So the elder said: I am here, O Messenger of Allah -- may my father and my mother be your sacrifice. So he said: Come and seek retaliation from me until you are satisfied. So the elder said: Uncover your stomach for me, O Messenger of Allah. So he (peace be upon him and his family) uncovered his stomach. The elder said: May my mother and my father be your sacrifice, O Messenger of Allah! Do you permit me to place my lips on your stomach? So he permitted him. So he said: I seek refuge from the Fire on the Day of the Fire for the place of retaliation on the stomach of the Messenger of Allah. So the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him and his family) said: O Suwada ibn Qays! Will you forgive or will you seek retaliation? So he said: Rather, I will forgive, O Messenger of Allah. So he (peace be upon him and his family) said: O Allah! Forgive Suwada ibn Qays just as he forgave Your Prophet Muhammad.",
    "ur": "",
    "tr": "",
    "fa": "",
    "id": "",
    "bn": "",
    "es": "",
    "fr": "",
    "de": "",
    "ru": "",
    "zh": ""
  }
}